title: 30 MINUTE INTERMEDIATE CALISTHENICS WORKOUT at Home | Follow Along
description:
This 30 minute intermediate calisthenics workout is a follow along you can do at home! In this bodyweight strength and mobility routine you'll work your entire body with a variety of exercises designed to challenge your strength and flexibility.

Level up your bodyweight training with this fully body workout that includes pistol squats, press up progressions, and more! I will guide you through the Calisthenics exercises, providing modifications to suit your fitness level, and technique tips making it suitable for beginners and intermediates.

comments: Doing your workouts for almost a year now and can clearly see the results. Been doing it in Guadalajara, Puerto Vallarta and CDMX, Mexico and Cologne, Munich and Berlin in Germany and in Malta and Paris, France. It truly travels the globe with me! Thanku for your great work!

49 yr old. I do tai chi regularly, and I started doing other types of excercies recently again, because it is getting more and more important for me to keep muscle mass in this age, so I googled for some home workout plan. I wanted sg that doesn't require weights, because I started doing excercies with smaller, for-home-use dumbbells too and I was looking for a plan for the days when I don't use dumbbells and a plan that would work the deeper muscles better.
Your channel was among the first 10 hits, I clicked on you first. I have just finished this routine.
In my opinion I gained enough experience to form a judgment and I found your program just appropriate for my goals. Thx!
Woman, 43, Sweden here. Just starting with calisthenics and I love it!

Spent 8 years in the United States Marine Corps. Got out and haven’t worked out since. Finally decided to get off my lazy ass and from behind my desk job and start doing some proper calisthenics. Gotta say, this is some PROPER Marine Corps stuff here. Thanks brother!
